description: There's an old saying that, 'The Devil is always busy.' Well this time the Dark Lord has outdone himself and has created a new entity that has the full Guardian team and both Neterus completely baffled. THAT is what's been going after the teams and infecting them. It has the essence of evil distilled down from his fallen Vampire Council, a little topspin from his exterminated favorite demon, The Thirteenth, with general regulation nastiness just for good measure. The problem the team has now is, how do they track something that can morph at will? Perhaps the bigger question is, once they find it, how the hell do they kill it?
name: The Hidden Darkness, Book Four: Ride Or Die

volume.name: L.A. Banks' Vampire Huntress: The Hidden Darkness

description: After his teammates' betrayal and the loss of another eye, Deathstroke must reunite the splintered group if they're to have any hope of escaping Drago's island. Meanwhile, Osiris and Isis return to Kahndaq to reclaim their thrones, and the Tattooed Man returns home to Liberty Hill, where he runs into Vixen.
name: Broken Promises, Part 3: Under Siege

description:
FEAR ITSELF TIE-IN

Loki, the great betrayer, the great destroyer has returned! But in all the nine realms there is no one who trusts him. Sadly, when he's the first to discover the dread secret behind FEAR ITSELF and issues forth a call to arms, none will heed his call. Thrill to the latest JIM installment as the younthened Trickster God makes his devious move for power and control!
name: Too Much Light Makes The Loki Go Blind

description: Doc and his team may be out of luck this time, up against the notoriously brutal Egyptian police, a horde of angry Mongols and a scheming Russian blonde. But leave it to Doc to find the bizarre secret that connects all their foes – and to find it while surrounded by ravenous, mind-controlled crocodiles!
name: Raise the Khan Chapter Two

description:
With Starro the Conqueror on the verge of complete victory, our rebel fighters Lobo, Vril Dox, Adam Strange, Starfire and the gang pull out all the stops in this series' bloody conclusion!

Starro has used his Starro spores to take over most of New Rann. He has Vril dox under his control, and his only real restince is Blackfire, Starfire, Captain Comet, and Adam Strange, who he seems to be able to handle until Lyrl releases his secret weapon, a suped up Tribulus, with the new abilty to short circuit Starro's spores.

Even thoughTribulus is destroying the spores outside Starro and Vril able to keep the REBEL heroes in a cornar. As a last ditch effort Adam is able to turn on Vril's homing devise for Tribulus and bring the Starro killer to them.

Meanwhile back on Psion Smite and Lobo have become friends and Smite explains there is a jump gate on Psion and that the stranded REBEL team can get to New Rann with it. After the team leaves for New Rann they tell the now freed Vril to push Starro threw the gate, where Lobo and Smite are waiting for him.

One Week Later. New Rann seems at peace, Lyrl has escaped again and Vril and Blackfire have picked up their relationship where it left off.
name: Starstruck, Conclusion

description: Superman meets Sin City as the "Grounded" storyline takes The Man of Steel to Las Vegas! But waiting there for Superman is an out-of-control Livewire, who has become more powerful and erratic than ever. Can Superman (with the help of Jimmy Olsen) shut her down before she shuts all of Vegas down, and more important, is Superman somehow responsible for her condition?
name: Grounded, Part Nine
Take Back the Stars

description:
SEASON'S BEATINGS!

Mega-City One - A future metropolis PLAGUED BY every crime imaginable. Keeping order are the Judges, a stern police force acting as judge, jury and executioner. Toughest of all is Judge Dredd. He is the law!

Featuring rare thrills from 2000 AD annuals and specials released in the early nineties, experience Dredd stories from talented writers such as Mark Millar (Kick Ass) and Simon Furman (Transformers), and stunning artwork by Cam Kennedy (Star Wars – Dark Empire), Greg Staples (Sl´ine) and Geoff Senior (Death's Head) amongst others.

THIS VOLUME INCLUDES THE STORIES FROM

Judge Dredd Mega Special 1990

2000AD Annual 1991

Judge Dredd Annual 1991

2000AD Winter Special 1990

Judge Dredd Mega-Special 1991

2000AD Sci Fi Special 1991

2000AD Yearbook 1992

2000AD Winter Special 1993

Creator Bios

name: Vol.3

description: Join the excitement with an ALL NEW "Free Comic Book Day" battle royal! Sonic goes to pay his respects for a fallen friend in the Southern Tundra and stumbles upon Ixis Naugus!  How has the evil wizard managed to return?  How can Sonic beat this magical master of the elements?  All this plus exclusive new data files to tell you just who's who!
name: Rematch!

volume.name: Sonic: The Rematch, Free Comic Book Day Edition

description: Today everyone knows Mickey Mouse as the cheerful ambassador of all things Disney.  But back in the 1930's, Mickey gained fame as a rough-and-tumble, two-fisted epic hero - an adventurous scrapper matching wits with mobsters, kidnappers, spies, and even (gulp!) city slickers!  And Mickey's greatest feats of derring-do took place in his daily comic strip, written and drawn by one of the greatest cartoonists of the 20th century - Floyd Gottfredson.
name: Pluto the Racer

volume.name: Walt Disney's Mickey Mouse [Free Comic Book Day]

description: The hunt for Cinderella's longtime nemesis leads her from the heat of equatorial Africa to the chilly ski slopes of Switzerland. Cinderella and her companion, the Russian Fable Ivan Durak, have managed to stay one step ahead of the deadly assassin so far – but is their luck about to run out?
name: Part Four

description: An all ages flip book from BOOM! On one side, experience Darkwing Duck! Reprinting the blockbuster sold-out first issue of the Darkwing Duck ongoing series. But don't forget to flip this comic over, or you'll miss Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers, reprinting the first issue of the critically acclaimed bestseller from BOOM! Two hit series, both all ages, one flip book of pure fun! Don't miss the return of the Disney Afternoon Revolution that grabbed the attention of Disney fans everywhere!
name: The Duck Knight Returns / Worldwide Rescue Part 1

volume.name: Darkwing Duck Free Comic Book Day Edition / Chip 'N' Dale Rescue Rangers Free Comic Book Day Edition

description: In the middle of a long Scandinavian winter, a solitary hunter stalks the forest for what seems like weeks on end. His elusive prey starts to take on added significance as the hunter descends into helplessness and despair, to the point that the skills of even this seasoned outdoorsman are put to the ultimate test. Lavishly illustrated by Matthew Woodson, whose illustrations have appeared in Wired, Spin, Penthouse, Glamour and more, "The Hunt" is destined to be one of the most memorable Northlanders stories to date.
name: The Hunt

description: Justin Bieber started his life in simple public housing, and he must balance his growing fame with his humble beginnings as he comes of age with millions of pre-teen girls screaming his name and tweeting his every move. Fame: Justin Bieber traces the career of Bieber, from YouTube sensation to Twitter mainstay, from his musical childhood in Ontario to his first headlining tour.

"Citizen Taylor," part 1 of 2! Back in the real world at last, Tom follows Lizzie and Savoy to New York and to the auction house of Christian Bolinbroke. Lots #1 to 200? The worldly goods of Wilson Taylor. And the only thing more dangerous than the other bidders is the auctioneer himself.
name: Citizen Taylor, Part One of Two

description: Fans of the Magic: The Gathering trading card game, as well as any fantasy reader, will devour this action-packed comic. Featuring content from the Planeswalker web comic series, as well as a preview of the upcoming Path of the Planeswalker II graphic novel, readers will get adventures from all their favorite Planeswalkers with lavish illustrations by some of the industry's best known artists such as Mark Texeira, Kev Walker, Christopher Moeller, and Steve Prescott. The Path of the Planeswalker II Preview represents the high quality story-telling and illustrations readers have come to expect from the world's most popular trading card game, Magic: The Gathering.
name: FCBD Preview

volume.name: Magic the Gathering: Path of the Planeswalker II Preview

description: The mind-bending crossover with X-23 comes to it's brutal conclusion as Daken is forced to decide which side he's on and X-23 is forced to decide whom she can trust. Unfortunately, this is Madripoor...is it safe to trust anyone? Meanwhile, Malcolm Colcord must make a decision of his own; one of life or death, with the fate of the potentially-revived Weapon X program hanging in the balance.
name: Collision, Pt. 4

description: With Cobra Commander deceased, long live Cobra Commander, but what everyone wants to know is, who will be the new Cobra Commander? The role must be filled and the deadliest and sneakiest Cobra elite will compete to become the new ruler. The deciding factor will be whoever kills the most G.I. Joes!
name: Cobra Civil War Part 1

description: Indicia reads Volume 7 issue 39

A horde of savage green Martians has surrounded the Warlord of Yorn in Dejah Thoris's city of Lesser Helium. No red Martian will come to the aid of a backstabbing tyrant like Yorn, but Yorn has a big surprise in store, one he paid a very high price for. While the siege rages on, Dejah Thoris fights to free her one-time enemy, the Jed of Greater Helium. Valian, Yorn's son, has thrown in his lot with Dejah. It's only a matter of time before his father finds out...
name: Colossus of Mars, Part 3 of 5: The Convocation

description: The celebration of 70 years of Walt Disney’s Comics continues as the Donald Duck "Pirate Gold" trilogy reaches its exciting conclusion! Enjoy plenty of pitfalls and paydays as Donald and his nephews star in an adventure that Scrooge McDuck himself would be proud of in this 1962 classic from Abramo and Giampaolo Barosso, “South Sea Shenanigans.” Never-before-printed in the US! Featuring an eye-popping cover by Ducks master Daan Jippes!
name: Donald Finds Pirate Gold... Again!

description: Marvel's Greatest Superhero Battles is a trade paperback that reprints various superhero battles from the early days of Marvel, all written by Stan Lee. Each issue it prefaced by Stan Lee. There are a total of 12 battles including Hulk versus the Thing, Dr. Strange versus Mordo, Spider-Man versus Kingpin and many more.

With a growing sense of uncertainty and despair gripping the nation--and the world--the remnants of the Initiative program are sworn in as federal agents charged with keeping the peace. Their ensuing actions, however, threaten to plunge America's young heroes into civil war! Featuring AVENGERS: THE INITIATIVE stars THOR GIRL, ULTRAGIRL, CLOUD 9, KOMODO and HARDBALL--plus FIRESTAR, GRAVITY and some very cool surprises--YOUTH IN REVOLT brings the horror of FEAR ITSELF to the doorstep of a generation!
name: Youth In Revolt: Part One

description: The future looks bright when brilliant and benevolent Dr. Light unveils his latest creations: the Robot Masters! But when the nefarious Dr. Wily steals them for his own sinister purposes, there is no one left to stop him; no one except Mega Man! Don’t miss the first issue of this brand new ongoing series!
name: Let The Games Begin!, Part One

volume.name: Origins of Marvel Comics by Stan Lee

name: Into the Blue part 3

volume.name: Little White Mouse: Into the Blue

name: Into the Blue part 2

volume.name: Little White Mouse: Into the Blue

description: Team Grimes is anything but safe behind the bars of the prison. Rick decides to hang Thomas Richards for the murder of Hershel's children and Patricia attempts to save him. Richards is shot dead by Maggie while Dexter and Andrew take back control of the prison with weapons obtained by Block A of the prison. It appears as if it is time for Team Grimes to leave the facility.

The group has a visitor, but is she friend, foe or worse? Where did she come from? How did she survive? Can she be trusted? This is the beginning of a new story arc, an excellent jumping-on point for new readers. The quest to rebuild civilization starts here.

Patience Confronts the Anti-Christ!

The moment Patience has been dreading has arrived. Slaying demons and battling evil cult members is righteous. Rebelling against a Church hierarchy she knows is corrupt is virtuous. But now, faced with executing a young boy who may bring about the end of the world, Patience will discover how far she's willing to go to wield the Spear of Destiny and bear the mantle of Magdalena…
name: Blood of the Lamb, Part 6

description: Part one of a two part spy crossover! Pranks and bad behavior are running wild in Riverdale! Agents Betty and Veronica soon discover the problems could be caused by coded messages hidden on the popular kids show Funtime USA! And the main culprit looks to be a lovable clown named Klutzy. Things look to get worse when Funtime USA makes a live stop in Riverdale! Continues next month in BETTY #192.
name: Spy Girlz - Back in Action! Part 1

description: With Orcus and his army outside of the city of Tallus and an angry mob out for her blood on the inside, Sela finds herself between a rock and a hard place with only one way out…unfortunately it means her being used as a human sacrifice. Her only ally is the High Priestess of the city but she has some major problems of her own to deal with…problems that give her a special connection to Sela. A connection that can save them both or lead to their ultimate doom.

Archie's friends get trapped in the Wonder Realm's online gaming world! With the help of Dilton's latest invention, Archie must save his friends! Once inside, Archie discovers cool inventions, wondrous creatures and a horrific danger threatening everyone inside the game - the Black Knight!
name: Adventures in the Wonder Realm, Part 2

description: The Food Strikes Back! Archie continues his search for his friends lost in the Wonder Realm and makes a shocking discovery! Jughead is not only living in a city made of food, but he has become king of the Food People! That is, until Archie reveals Jughead’s true nature…
name: Adventures in the Wonder Realm, Part 3

description: “Adventures in the Wonder Realm” continue as Archie, Jughead and Betty fight for their lives against angry food and rock creatures standing between them and freedom! Will Veronica and their new friend Cheroby help the team in completing all the different levels? Or will they be lost in the Wonder Realm forever?
name: Adventures in Wonder Realm, Part 4

description: The thrilling conclusion to Archie's Adventures in the Wonder Realm is here! As Archie, Jughead, Betty, Veronica and their new friend Cheroby desperately fight to get home, they must cross dangerous lands and battle terrifying creatures. This all leads up to the final showdown with the dreaded Black Knight!
name: Adventures in Wonder Realm, Part 5

description: Atomic Robo and his followers find themselves getting more than they bargained for at national science fair when Dr. Dinosaur comes to steal Emma Armstrong's science project for his own insidious purposes. In addition this issue offers a glimpse into the world of Foster Broussard and the Demons of the Gold Rush (to be on comic shelves in May) as well as Moon Girl.
name: National Science Fair; Demons of the Gold Rush; Moon Girl

volume.name: Atomic Robo / Foster Broussard / Moon Girl Free Comic Book Day 2011

description:
An all-star lineup of creators brings you the origins of Marvel's greatest heroes! Short, accessible origin stories you'll want to cut out and tape up on your wall!

From the Avengers to the X-Men! From Iron Man, Thor, the Fantastic Four and Spider-Man to Hulk, Deadpool, Black Widow and the Punisher! Cyclops! Wolverine! Magneto!

They're all here! Plus: In the aftermath of SIEGE, Steve Rogers assesses the state of Earth's heroes, villains and mutants in almost 200 pages of character files!

Collects:

ORIGINS OF MARVEL COMICS

ORIGINS OF MARVEL COMICS: X-MEN

HEROIC AGE: SUPER HEROES

HEROIC AGE: VILLAINS

HEROIC AGE: X-MEN
